{
  "message": "fix(js): correct ripgrep TypeScript file detection\n\nThe type narrowing check was failing silently because `rg -q` without\na search pattern hangs waiting for stdin. Changed to `rg --files` which\ncorrectly lists matching files.\n\nAlso updated js-edge-cases test expectation: edge-case files (unicode,\ntimezone, floating-point bugs) are warnings not critical security issues.\n\n\ud83e\udd16 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "af81fdfae65f64a2dee2d719cd6bd06521c8697e",
      "filename": "modules/ubs-js.sh",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 2,
      "deletions": 1,
      "changes": 3,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/ultimate_bug_scanner/blob/355a78d0afe2a34e05373e1281f77244e564fdd7/modules%2Fubs-js.sh",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/ultimate_bug_scanner/raw/355a78d0afe2a34e05373e1281f77244e564fdd7/modules%2Fubs-js.sh",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Dicklesworthstone/ultimate_bug_scanner/contents/modules%2Fubs-js.sh?ref=355a78d0afe2a34e05373e1281f77244e564fdd7",
      "patch": "@@ -1149,7 +1149,8 @@ run_type_narrowing_checks() {\n   fi\n   local has_ts=0\n   if command -v rg >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n-    if rg -q --hidden \"${RG_EXCLUDES[@]}\" -g '*.ts' -g '*.tsx' \"$PROJECT_DIR\" 2>/dev/null; then\n+    # Use --files to list matching files (rg -q needs a pattern to search for, which we don't have)\n+    if rg --files --hidden \"${RG_EXCLUDES[@]}\" -g '*.ts' -g '*.tsx' \"$PROJECT_DIR\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q .; then\n       has_ts=1\n     fi\n   else"
    },
